Hql query 
HQL is an object-oriented query language used in Hibernate to perform database operations using entity classes instead of tables.
HQL (Hibernate Query Language) is a query language used in Hibernate to interact with the database using Java objects instead of table names.
It is similar to SQL, but it works with entity classes and their properties.

1️⃣ What is HQL?

HQL allows you to:

Retrieve data,Insert data,Update data,Delete data

Example:
 Basic HQL Syntax
Session session = sessionFactory.openSession();
Query query = session.createQuery("FROM Employee");
List<Employee> list = query.list();
Common HQL Queries
1. Select All Records
Query q = session.createQuery("FROM Employee");
List<Employee> list = q.list();

Equivalent SQL:
SELECT * FROM employee;
2. Select Specific Fields
Query q = session.createQuery("SELECT e.name, e.salary FROM Employee e");
List<Object[]> list = q.list();
3. Where Condition
Query q = session.createQuery("FROM Employee WHERE salary > 50000");
List<Employee> list = q.list();
4. Named Parameter
Query q = session.createQuery("FROM Employee WHERE name = :name");
q.setParameter("name", "John");
List<Employee> list = q.list();
5. Update Query
Transaction tx = session.beginTransaction();
Query q = session.createQuery(
    "UPDATE Employee SET salary = 60000 WHERE id = 1");
int result = q.executeUpdate();
tx.commit();
6. Delete Query
Transaction tx = session.beginTransaction();
Query q = session.createQuery(
    "DELETE FROM Employee WHERE id = 1");

q.executeUpdate();

tx.commit();
4️⃣ Important Points
Uses entity class name, not table name
Uses object properties, not column names

Example Entity
@Entity
public class Employee {

    @Id
    private int id;
    private String name;
    private double salary;

}

HQL Query:
FROM Employee WHERE salary > 40000
