@autowire and @qualifier

@Autowired is used for automatic dependency injection in Spring. It tells Spring to inject a bean into a class automatically.”

🔹 How It Works
Spring searches the application context for a bean of the matching type.
Injects it by type by default.
📌 Example
@Component
public class ServiceA { }

@Component
public class Consumer {
    @Autowired
    private ServiceA serviceA;  // Spring injects ServiceA automatically
}
✅ 2. @Qualifier

“@Qualifier is used along with @Autowired when there are multiple beans of the same type, and we want to specify which bean to inject.”

📌 Example
@Component("service1")
public class ServiceA { }

@Component("service2")
public class ServiceAImpl extends ServiceA { }

@Component
public class Consumer {
    @Autowired
    @Qualifier("service2")  // specify exactly which bean to inject
    private ServiceA service;
}
🧠 How to Explain in Interview

“@Autowired injects a dependency automatically by type.
When multiple beans of the same type exist, we use @Qualifier to tell Spring which exact bean to inject.”


“@Autowired = inject by type automatically, @Qualifier = specify which bean when multiple exist.”

